    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1890-07-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1890-07-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="395"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d395">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Ryan</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Blaine</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-07-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 30, 1890</date>. (Received August
                        11.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 360.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to advise the Department that on
                    the 29th instant Señor Geronimo Pou, special agent of Señor Carlos Ezeta,
                    provisional president of Salvador, in an interview upon the subject of
                    hostilities between Salvador and Guatemala, said that it would be agreeable to
                    Salvador if the Government of the United States would interpose its friendly
                    offices to stop further bloodshed and restore peace upon the basis of the
                    autonomy, integrity of territory, and independence of that Republic,
                    notwithstanding the fact that the Salvadorian army had defeated the Guatemalan
                    troops in every engagement, numbering eleven battles and skirmishes, and was
                    then in strong position upon Guatemalan territory 12 leagues from the
                    border.</p>
                <p>I assured him that I would communicate what he said to the Department of State at
                    Washington, and thereupon I wired you.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thos. Ryan.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
